	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Two possibilities:<br /><br />A. It disables NMI before calling the test routine and reenables NMI afterward.<br />B. The NMI handler doesn't write to any RAM locations that the test routine uses. In a lot of my programs, for example, NMI just increments one location in zero page.

		

